<ol><li>The <b>potential energy</b> at displacement&nbsp;\(x\)&nbsp;is given by\[E_P=\frac{1}{2}kx^2\]</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>total energy</b>&nbsp;of the system is constant and equal to its&nbsp;<b>maximum potential energy</b>.\[E_T=E_P+E_K=\frac{1}{2}kA^2\]</li><li>So the&nbsp;<b>kinetic energy</b>&nbsp;is given by\[E_K=\frac{1}{2}k(A^2-x^2)\]</li></ol>